00:49:49,740 --> 00:49:53,820
Well, if he's the only Jew that has jurisdiction over that courtyard...

1009
00:49:53,900 --> 00:49:58,260
No, they all, the other ones do too. In practical terms, this

1010
00:49:58,260 --> 00:49:59,140
courtyard is shared by

1011
00:50:07,020 --> 00:50:07,260
the other

1012
00:50:15,940 --> 00:50:18,920
ten people. I know, but it's a little funny because practically you

1013
00:50:18,920 --> 00:50:22,280
have all these different people using the courtyard, and that's not conceived

1014
00:50:22,280 --> 00:50:24,560
as properly—I know, I'm just saying we'll have to see that. So

1015
00:50:24,560 --> 00:50:27,300
one is a question about why is one Jew better than two

1016
00:50:27,300 --> 00:50:30,940
Jews? And number two is, in a practical sense, a courtyard that's

1017
00:50:30,940 --> 00:50:34,240
shared by multiple people, that that should be a non-issue is a

1018
00:50:34,240 --> 00:50:36,360
funny idea, but that's what the משנה *Mishnah* implies. So we'll see

1019
00:50:36,360 --> 00:50:38,780
more about that in the גמרא *Gemara*. And now we have a

1020
00:50:38,780 --> 00:50:42,157
story about an—again talking about case law, an actual story. אמר רבן

1021
00:50:42,157 --> 00:50:45,044
גמליאל *Amar Rabban Gamliel*, מעשה בצדוקי אחד *Maaseh bitzeduki echad*, there was

