00:50:45,044 --> 00:50:48,475
a story of a case about a Sadducee, שהיה דר עמנו במבוי

1023
00:50:48,475 --> 00:50:51,700
*shehayah dar immanu bamavoi*, that he was part of, you know—not courtyard

1024
00:50:51,900 --> 00:50:54,129
but the מבוי *mavoi*, like a courtyard that opened into an alleyway,

1025
00:50:54,129 --> 00:50:58,020
בירושלים *biYerushalayim*. ואמר לנו אבא *Ve'amar lanu Abba*, and our father said

1026
00:50:58,020 --> 00:51:01,347
to us, מהרו והוציאו את הכלים למבוי עד שלא יוציא ויאסר עליכם

1027
00:51:01,347 --> 00:51:04,233
*Maharu vehotziu et hakelim lamavoi ad shelo yotzi veye'aser aleichem*. Go quickly,

1028
00:51:04,233 --> 00:51:06,280
take all your vessels out into the—into the מבוי *mavoi* so that

1029
00:51:06,280 --> 00:51:08,860
he doesn't take his stuff out and make it forbidden on you.

1030
00:51:08,920 --> 00:51:12,880
Now what the heck is going on here? So what רש"י *Rashi*

1031
00:51:12,880 --> 00:51:17,980
says is that he is assuming that a צדוקי *Tzeduki*, somebody who

1032
00:51:17,980 --> 00:51:22,080
is not מודה בעירוב *modeh be'eruv*, is not like the non-Jew. The

1033
00:51:22,080 --> 00:51:25,720
non-Jew, if you want to make an עירוב *eruv*, you have to

1034
00:51:25,720 --> 00:51:28,549
rent his space. Again, not in the משנה *Mishnah*. But the צדוקי

1035
00:51:28,549 --> 00:51:30,380
*Tzeduki*, if you want an עירוב *eruv*, it's enough for him to

1036
00:51:30,380 --> 00:51:33,560
be מבטל רשות *mevattel reshut*. He's Jewish, he just doesn't buy in.

1037
00:51:33,740 --> 00:51:36,680
So he can't be an active member of the עירוב *eruv*, but

1038
00:51:36,680 --> 00:51:39,437
he can say, you know what, I waive my rights. That he

1039
00:51:39,437 --> 00:51:41,660
can say. You don't have to actually have a formal rental agreement.

1040
00:51:42,080 --> 00:51:44,260
On the one hand you don't need that much, on the other

1041
00:51:44,260 --> 00:51:47,149
hand he can't actually be an active member of the עירוב *eruv*,

1042
00:51:47,149 --> 00:51:49,700
but what he can say is, I waive my rights. The problem

1043
00:51:49,700 --> 00:51:52,980
of saying I waive my rights is that he can reclaim his

1044
00:51:52,980 --> 00:51:56,200
rights. So that's the issue. So it worked by him waiving his

1045
00:51:56,200 --> 00:51:59,220
rights. It's not a complete problem, but we have to stop him

1046
00:51:59,220 --> 00:52:02,609
from reclaiming his rights. So therefore what we do is, when שבת

1047
00:52:02,609 --> 00:52:06,400
*Shabbat* begins, we go out there and we assert our rights in

1048
00:52:06,400 --> 00:52:10,680
the courtyard so he can't go ahead and change his mind. Like

1049
00:52:10,680 --> 00:52:13,400
it's—if you were מפקיר *mafkir* something and before anybody picked it up,

1050
00:52:13,440 --> 00:52:15,740
you grabbed it back. So you don't want that to happen. So

1051
00:52:15,740 --> 00:52:17,995
we have to grab what he was מפקיר *mafkir*. Every שבת *Shabbat*?

1052
00:52:18,320 --> 00:52:20,937
Every שבת *Shabbat* we would have to do this. Okay. How does

1053
00:52:20,937 --> 00:52:21,803
that work, though?

1054
00:52:21,803 --> 00:52:23,535
Like how do they prevent him

1055
00:52:24,800 --> 00:52:29,020
from—no, after presumably they've asserted their rights, he can now come and

1056
00:52:29,020 --> 00:52:31,500
use it during the שבת *Shabbat*, but after they've already established that

1057
00:52:31,500 --> 00:52:34,060
for this שבת *Shabbat* we are the ones that have, you know,

1058
00:52:34,080 --> 00:52:36,589
rights over this space. So it's like if you were מפקיר *mafkir*

1059
00:52:36,589 --> 00:52:38,680
an object and I picked it up, if you picked it up

1060
00:52:38,680 --> 00:52:41,580
afterwards it would still be mine. So now the courtyard isn't there

1061
00:52:41,580 --> 00:52:45,389
at—from perpetuity, but for the purpose of this שבת *Shabbat*, this כותי

1062
00:52:45,389 --> 00:52:48,160
*Kutti* said I waive my rights, and if we then showed that

1063
00:52:48,160 --> 00:52:52,480
we were taking sort of—asserting our rights to it for שבת *Shabbat*,

1064
00:52:52,560 --> 00:52:55,120
then he's not in a position to reclaim his rights for the

1065
00:52:55,120 --> 00:52:58,120
שבת *Shabbat*. That's at least the assumption. So it has a lot

1066
00:52:58,120 --> 00:52:59,620
of things that are not in this משנה *Mishnah* that are being

1067
00:52:59,620 --> 00:53:03,500
assumed. A צדוקי *Tzeduki* is different than a non-Jew, maybe even different

1068
00:53:03,500 --> 00:53:04,980
than a כותי *Kutti*, we can discuss that.

1069
00:53:06,000 --> 00:53:07,640
You don't have to rent it from him, which wasn't in the

1070
00:53:07,640 --> 00:53:10,060
משנה *Mishnah* anyway, the renting. He can waive his rights, but you

1071
00:53:10,060 --> 00:53:14,000
have to make sure he doesn't—he doesn't reclaim them. Okay, let's just

1072
00:53:14,000 --> 00:53:16,452
read the other case. רבי יהודה אומר *Rabbi Yehudah omer*, רבי יהודה

1073
00:53:16,452 --> 00:53:19,220
*Rabbi Yehudah* said, בלשון אחר *belashon acher*, he had a different version

1074
00:53:19,220 --> 00:53:22,418
of the story. מהרו ועשו צרכיכם במבוי עד שלא יוציא ויאסר עליכם

1075
00:53:22,418 --> 00:53:25,400
*Maharu ve'asu tzorcheichem bamavoi ad shelo yotzi veye'aser aleichem*. Take care of

1076
00:53:25,400 --> 00:53:27,880
anything you need to do in the מבוי *mavoi* until he

1077
00:53:28,1000 --> 00:53:32,000
goes—because he'll come out—he'll come out and he'll make it forbidden. And

1078
00:53:32,000 --> 00:53:34,840
the way the גמרא *Gemara* explains the difference is that he actually

1079
00:53:34,840 --> 00:53:39,180
says that even after you've used the courtyard, he can reclaim his

1080
00:53:39,180 --> 00:53:42,797
rights. He can always reclaim his rights. So basically it's גורנישט העלפן

1081
00:53:42,797 --> 00:53:45,580
*gornisht helfn*. Even if he waives his rights, all you can do

1082
00:53:45,580 --> 00:53:48,360
is use it until he changes his mind. So what he actually

1083
00:53:48,360 --> 00:53:51,700
said is, better—better make the best out of it now, because as

1084
00:53:51,700 --> 00:53:53,860
soon as he changes his mind you're in trouble. So what we

1085
00:53:53,860 --> 00:53:57,029
have here is a couple of fascinating things. A non-Jew or מי

1086
00:53:57,029 --> 00:53:58,920
שאינו מודה בעירוב *mi she'eino modeh be'eruv* cannot be an active part

1087
00:53:58,920 --> 00:54:02,880
of the—of the עירוב *eruv*. What can they do? Not really spelled

1088
00:54:02,880 --> 00:54:05,389
out at all in the משנה *Mishnah*. We'll see in the גמרא

1089
00:54:05,389 --> 00:54:08,260
*Gemara* that from a non-Jew you can rent it. From a—somebody who's

1090
00:54:08,260 --> 00:54:10,700
not מודה בעירוב *modeh be'eruv* you might have another alternative, which is

1091
00:54:10,700 --> 00:54:13,400
to let him waive his rights. And then what's being debated here

1092
00:54:13,400 --> 00:54:17,180
is after he's waived his rights, is there a way to secure

1093
00:54:17,180 --> 00:54:20,240
that for all of שבת *Shabbat* or is he always in a

1094
00:54:20,240 --> 00:54:24,460
position to, you know, reassert his rights and to reverse it? And

1095
00:54:24,460 --> 00:54:26,880
then we also have the really fascinating issue of the difference between

1096
00:54:26,880 --> 00:54:28,900
two Jews and one Jew and how that's going to play out.

1097
00:54:28,900 --> 00:54:30,420
So it's going to be a lot of דפים *dappim* and we

